  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients who have provided written informed consent

          -  Patients older than 60 years

          -  Patients presenting a closed intra-articular fracture of the distal radius with a
             dorsal tilt (stages B2, C1, C2 and C3)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Adults under guardianship

          -  Patients without national health insurance cover

          -  Pregnant or breast-feeding women

          -  Patients presenting other injuries in the same upper limb

          -  Patients presenting injuries of the wrist or hand (scapholunate injury, fracture of
             the carpal bone or fingers)

          -  Pre-trauma paralysis of the limb

          -  Open fracture

          -  Fracture with palmer tilt or extra-articular
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
